OL,4,Cstill leave #189m deficit, Swann warns
OL,6,FThe analysis by trusts said possible
OL,7,F"contingency" savings measures
OL,8,Fincluded recruitment freezes for "non-
OL,9,Ffrontline" staff and further
OL,10,Freductions in agency and locum costs,
OL,11,Fbut the analysis states that such
OL,12,Fsavings "will be challenging in a
OL,13,Fsingle year and may not be achievable
OL,14,Fin their entirety".
OL,16,F"This leaves a remaining and
OL,17,Fsignificant deficit of #189m (assuming
OL,18,Fno pay increase in 2024/25)," it said,
OL,19,Fbut warned that this level of savings
OL,20,F"cannot be achieved without high/
OL,21,Fcatastrophic impact measures".
